Description of incident: Six CDs missing from                the ID Badging office at Seattle-Tacoma International Airport hold                the personal information of 6,939 airport workers. The data include                names, addresses, birth dates, SSNs and driver's license numbers,                telephone numbers, employer information, and height/weight. The                data on the disks were scanned from paper applications for airport                badges. The port learned of the missing disks on September 18 and                sent letters to the affected employees on Oct. 2.
